ciscoIetfIsisMIB.name: ciscoIetfIsisMIB

revisions.description: Corrected DESCRIPTION clause for ciiAreaAddrTable, ciiAreaAddrEntry, ciiAreaAddr and for ciiSysLevelOverloadState based on similar definitions in draft-ietf-isis-wg-mib-18.txt.

ciscoIetfIsisMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-clns@cisco.com
ciscoIetfIsisMIB.description: This document describes a management information base for the IS-IS Routing protocol, as described in ISO 10589, when it is used to construct routing tables for IP networks, as described in RFC 1195. This MIB is entirely based upon the IETF draft draft-ietf-isis-wg-mib-16.

CiiOSINSAddress.name: CiiOSINSAddress
CiiOSINSAddress.description: OSI Network Service Address, e.g. NSAP, SNPA, or Network Entity Title

CiiAdminState.name: CiiAdminState
CiiAdminState.description: Type used in enabling and disabling a row. Values match those in RFC 2863.

CiiLSPBuffSize.name: CiiLSPBuffSize
CiiLSPBuffSize.description: Integer sub range for LSP size.

CiiSupportedProtocol.name: CiiSupportedProtocol
CiiSupportedProtocol.description: Types of network protocol supported by Integrated IS-IS. The values for ISO8473 and IP are those registered for these protocols in ISO TR9577.

CiiDefaultMetric.name: CiiDefaultMetric
CiiDefaultMetric.description: Integer sub-range for default metric for single hop. ISO 10589 provides for 4 types of metric. Only the 'default' metric is used in practice.

CiiWideMetric.name: CiiWideMetric
CiiWideMetric.description: Wide Metric for IS Neighbors. ISO 10589 provides a 6 bit metric. Traffic Engineering extensions provide 24 bit metrics.

CiiFullMetric.name: CiiFullMetric
CiiFullMetric.description: Full Metric for IP Routes. Traffic Engineering extensions provide 32 bit metrics.

CiiMetricType.name: CiiMetricType
CiiMetricType.description: Is this an Internal or External Metric?

CiiMetricStyle.name: CiiMetricStyle
CiiMetricStyle.description: Do we use 1195 style Metrics or wide metrics.

CiiPDUHeader.name: CiiPDUHeader
CiiPDUHeader.description: A block to contain the header from a PDU.

CiiUnsigned16TC.name: CiiUnsigned16TC
CiiUnsigned16TC.description: An Unsigned32 further restricted to 16 Bits. Note that the ASN.1 BER encoding may still require 24 Bits for some values.

CiiUnsigned8TC.name: CiiUnsigned8TC
CiiUnsigned8TC.description: An Unsigned32 further restricted to 8 Bits. Note that the ASN.1 BER encoding may still require 16 Bits for some values.

ciiSysVersion.name: ciiSysVersion
ciiSysVersion.description: The version number of the IS-IS protocol that is implemented.

ciiSysType.name: ciiSysType
ciiSysType.description: At which levels is the Intermediate System running? This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior.

ciiSysID.name: ciiSysID
ciiSysID.description: The ID for this Intermediate System. This value is appended to each of the area addresses to form the Network Entity Titles. The derivation of a value for this object is implementation-specific. Some implementations may automatically assign values and not permit an SNMP write, while others may require the value to be set manually.

ciiSysMaxPathSplits.name: ciiSysMaxPathSplits
ciiSysMaxPathSplits.description: Maximum number of paths with equal routing metric value which it is permitted to split between. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior.

ciiSysMaxLSPGenInt.name: ciiSysMaxLSPGenInt
ciiSysMaxLSPGenInt.description: Maximum interval, in seconds, between generated LSPs by this Intermediate System. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior. The value must be greater than any value configured for ciiSysLevelMinLSPGenInt, and should be at least 300 seconds less than ciiSysMaxAge.

ciiSysPollESHelloRate.name: ciiSysPollESHelloRate
ciiSysPollESHelloRate.description: The value, in seconds, to be used for the suggested ES configuration timer in ISH PDUs when soliciting the ES configuration.

ciiSysWaitTime.name: ciiSysWaitTime
ciiSysWaitTime.description: Number of seconds to delay in 'waiting' state before entering 'on' state. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior.

ciiSysAdminState.name: ciiSysAdminState
ciiSysAdminState.description: The administrative state of this Intermediate System. Setting this object to the value 'on' when its current value is 'off' enables the Intermediate System.

ciiSysL2toL1Leaking.name: ciiSysL2toL1Leaking
ciiSysL2toL1Leaking.description: If true, allow the router to leak L2 routes into L1.

ciiSysMaxAge.name: ciiSysMaxAge
ciiSysMaxAge.description: Value to place in RemainingLifeTime field of the LSPs we generate. This should be at least 300 seconds greater than ciiSysMaxLSPGenInt.

ciiSysReceiveLSPBufferSize.name: ciiSysReceiveLSPBufferSize
ciiSysReceiveLSPBufferSize.description: Size of the largest Buffer we are designed or configured to store. This should be at least as big as the maximum ciiSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize supported by the system. If resources allow, we will store and flood LSPs larger than ciiSysReceiveLSPBufferSize, as this can help avoid problems in networks with different values for ciiSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize.

ciiManAreaAddrTable.name: ciiManAreaAddrTable
ciiManAreaAddrTable.description: The set of manual area addresses configured on this Intermediate System.

ciiManAreaAddrEntry.name: ciiManAreaAddrEntry
ciiManAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one area address manually configured on this system

ciiManAreaAddr.name: ciiManAreaAddr
ciiManAreaAddr.description: A manually configured area address for this system. This object follows the index behavior. Note: an index for the entry {1, {49.0001} active} in this table would be the ordered pair (1, (0x03 0x49 0x00 0x01)), as the length of an Octet string is part of the OID.

ciiManAreaAddrExistState.name: ciiManAreaAddrExistState
ciiManAreaAddrExistState.description: The state of the ciiManAreaAddrEntry. This object follows the Row Status behavior. If the ciiSysAdminState for this Intermediate System is 'on', and an attempt is made to set this object to the value 'destroy' or 'notInService' when this is the only ciiManAreaAddrEntry in state 'active' for this Intermediate System should return inconsistentValue.

ciiAreaAddrTable.name: ciiAreaAddrTable
ciiAreaAddrTable.description: The union of the sets of area addresses reported in all Level 1 LSPs with fragment number zero generated by this Intermediate System, or received from other Intermediate Systems which are reachable via Level 1 routing.

ciiAreaAddrEntry.name: ciiAreaAddrEntry
ciiAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one area address reported in a Level 1 LSP generated or received by this Intermediate System.

ciiAreaAddr.name: ciiAreaAddr
ciiAreaAddr.description: An area address reported in a Level 1 LSP.

ciiSysProtSuppTable.name: ciiSysProtSuppTable
ciiSysProtSuppTable.description: This table contains the manually configured set of protocols supported by this Intermediate System.

ciiSysProtSuppEntry.name: ciiSysProtSuppEntry
ciiSysProtSuppEntry.description: Each entry contains one protocol supported by this Intermediate System.

ciiSysProtSuppProtocol.name: ciiSysProtSuppProtocol
ciiSysProtSuppProtocol.description: One supported protocol. This object follows the index behavior.

ciiSysProtSuppExistState.name: ciiSysProtSuppExistState
ciiSysProtSuppExistState.description: The state of the ciiSysProtSuppEntry. This object follows the RowStatus behavior.

ciiSummAddrTable.name: ciiSummAddrTable
ciiSummAddrTable.description: The set of IP summary addresses to use in forming summary TLVs originated by this Intermediate System. An administrator may use a summary address to combine and modify IP Reachability announcements. If the Intermediate system can reach any subset of the summary address, the summary address will be announced instead, at the configured metric.

ciiSummAddrEntry.name: ciiSummAddrEntry
ciiSummAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP summary address.

ciiSummAddressType.name: ciiSummAddressType
ciiSummAddressType.description: The Type of IP address for this summary address. This object follows the index behavior.

ciiSummAddress.name: ciiSummAddress
ciiSummAddress.description: The IP Address value for this summary address. This object follows the index behavior.

ciiSummAddrPrefixLen.name: ciiSummAddrPrefixLen
ciiSummAddrPrefixLen.description: The Length of the IP NetMask for this summary address.

ciiSummAddrExistState.name: ciiSummAddrExistState
ciiSummAddrExistState.description: The existence state of this summary address. This object follows the row status behavior.

ciiSummAddrMetric.name: ciiSummAddrMetric
ciiSummAddrMetric.description: The metric value to announce this summary address with in LSPs generated by this system.

ciiSummAddrFullMetric.name: ciiSummAddrFullMetric
ciiSummAddrFullMetric.description: The wide metric value to announce this summary address with in LSPs generated by this system.

ciiRedistributeAddrTable.name: ciiRedistributeAddrTable
ciiRedistributeAddrTable.description: This table provides criteria to decide if a route should be leaked from L2 to L1 when Domain Wide Prefix leaking is enabled. Addresses that match the summary mask in the table will be announced at L1 by routers when ciiSysL2toL1Leaking is enabled. Routes that fall into the ranges specified are announced as is, without being summarized. Routes that do not match a summary mask are not announced.

ciiRedistributeAddrEntry.name: ciiRedistributeAddrEntry
ciiRedistributeAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP summary address to manage leaking L2 addresses into L1.

ciiRedistributeAddrType.name: ciiRedistributeAddrType
ciiRedistributeAddrType.description: The Type of IP address for this summary address. This object follows the index behavior.

ciiRedistributeAddrAddress.name: ciiRedistributeAddrAddress
ciiRedistributeAddrAddress.description: The IP Address value for this summary address. This object follows the index behavior.

ciiRedistributeAddrPrefixLen.name: ciiRedistributeAddrPrefixLen
ciiRedistributeAddrPrefixLen.description: The Length of the IP NetMask for this summary address.

ciiRedistributeAddrExistState.name: ciiRedistributeAddrExistState
ciiRedistributeAddrExistState.description: The existence state of this summary address. This object follows the row status behavior.

ciiRouterTable.name: ciiRouterTable
ciiRouterTable.description: The set of hostnames and router ID.

ciiRouterEntry.name: ciiRouterEntry
ciiRouterEntry.description: Each entry tracks information about one peer at one level.

ciiRouterSysID.name: ciiRouterSysID
ciiRouterSysID.description: The System ID of the Router Peer.

ciiRouterLevel.name: ciiRouterLevel
ciiRouterLevel.description: The level of this Intermediate System.

ciiRouterHostName.name: ciiRouterHostName
ciiRouterHostName.description: The hostname listed in LSP, or zero-length string if none.

ciiRouterID.name: ciiRouterID
ciiRouterID.description: The Router ID of the Peer found in LSP, or zero if none.

ciiSysLevelTable.name: ciiSysLevelTable
ciiSysLevelTable.description: Level specific information about the System.

ciiSysLevelEntry.name: ciiSysLevelEntry
ciiSysLevelEntry.description: Describe variables defined for Area or Domain.

ciiSysLevelIndex.name: ciiSysLevelIndex
ciiSysLevelIndex.description: The level that this entry describes.

ciiSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize.name: ciiSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize
ciiSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize.description: The maximum size of LSPs and SNPs originated by this Intermediate System at this level. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior.

ciiSysLevelMinLSPGenInt.name: ciiSysLevelMinLSPGenInt
ciiSysLevelMinLSPGenInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between successive generation of LSPs with the same LSPID at this level by this Intermediate System. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior.

ciiSysLevelOverloadState.name: ciiSysLevelOverloadState
ciiSysLevelOverloadState.description: The state of the database at this level. The value 'off' indicates that IS-IS is not active at this level. The value 'on' indicates that IS-IS is active at this level, and not overloaded. The value 'waiting' indicates a database that is low on an essential resource, such as memory. The administrator may force the state to 'overloaded' by setting the object ciiSysLevelSetOverload. If the state is 'waiting' or 'overloaded', we originate LSPs with the Overload bit set.

ciiSysLevelSetOverload.name: ciiSysLevelSetOverload
ciiSysLevelSetOverload.description: Administratively set the overload bit for the level. The overload bit will continue to be set if the implementation runs out of memory, independent of this variable

ciiSysLevelSetOverloadUntil.name: ciiSysLevelSetOverloadUntil
ciiSysLevelSetOverloadUntil.description: If set, the overload bit should be set, and cleared after sysUpTime exceeds this value.

ciiSysLevelMetricStyle.name: ciiSysLevelMetricStyle
ciiSysLevelMetricStyle.description: Which style of Metric do we generate in our LSPs at this level? This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior.

ciiSysLevelSPFConsiders.name: ciiSysLevelSPFConsiders
ciiSysLevelSPFConsiders.description: Which style of Metric do we consider in our SPF computation at this level?

ciiSysLevelTEEnabled.name: ciiSysLevelTEEnabled
ciiSysLevelTEEnabled.description: Do we do Traffic Engineering at this level?

ciiNextCircIndex.name: ciiNextCircIndex
ciiNextCircIndex.description: This object is used to assign values to ciiCircIndex as described in 'Textual Conventions for SNMPv2'. The network manager reads this object, and then writes the value back as the ciiCircIndex in a SET that creates a new instance of ciiCircEntry. If the SET fails with the code 'inconsistentValue', then the process must be repeated; If the SET succeeds, then the object is incremented, and the new ciiCircEntry is created according to the manager's directions.

ciiCircTable.name: ciiCircTable
ciiCircTable.description: The table of circuits used by this Intermediate System.

ciiCircEntry.name: ciiCircEntry
ciiCircEntry.description: An ciiCircEntry exists for each circuit used by Integrated IS-IS on this system.

ciiCircIndex.name: ciiCircIndex
ciiCircIndex.description: The identifier of this circuit, unique within the Intermediate System. This object follows the index behavior. This is for SNMP Indexing purposes only and need not have any relation to any protocol value.

ciiCircIfIndex.name: ciiCircIfIndex
ciiCircIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex for the interface to which this circuit corresponds. This object cannot be modified after creation

ciiCircIfSubIndex.name: ciiCircIfSubIndex
ciiCircIfSubIndex.description: A specifier for the part of the interface ifIndex to which this circuit corresponds, such as a DLCI or VPI/VCI. This object cannot be modified after creation

ciiCircAdminState.name: ciiCircAdminState
ciiCircAdminState.description: The administrative state of the circuit. This object follows the CiiAdminState behavior.

ciiCircExistState.name: ciiCircExistState
ciiCircExistState.description: The existence state of this circuit. This object follows the RowStatus behavior. Setting the state to 'notInService' halts the generation and processing of IS-IS protocol PDUs on this circuit. Setting the state to 'destroy' will also erase any configuration associated with the circuit.

ciiCircType.name: ciiCircType
ciiCircType.description: The type of the circuit. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior. The type specified must be compatible with the type of the interface defined by the value of ciiCircIfIndex.

ciiCircExtDomain.name: ciiCircExtDomain
ciiCircExtDomain.description: If true, suppress normal transmission of and interpretation of Intra-domain IS-IS PDUs on this circuit.

ciiCircLevel.name: ciiCircLevel
ciiCircLevel.description: Indicates which type of packets will be sent and accepted on this circuit. The values used will be modified by the settings of ciiSysType. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled behavior.

ciiCircPassiveCircuit.name: ciiCircPassiveCircuit
ciiCircPassiveCircuit.description: Should we include this interface in LSPs, even if it is not running the IS-IS Protocol?

ciiCircMeshGroupEnabled.name: ciiCircMeshGroupEnabled
ciiCircMeshGroupEnabled.description: Is this port a member of a mesh group, or blocked? Circuits in the same mesh group act as a virtual multiaccess network. LSPs seen on one circuit in a mesh group will not be flooded to another circuit in the same mesh group.

ciiCircMeshGroup.name: ciiCircMeshGroup
ciiCircMeshGroup.description: Circuits in the same mesh group act as a virtual multiaccess network. LSPs seen on one circuit in a mesh group will not be flooded to another circuit in the same mesh group. If ciiCircMeshGroupEnabled is inactive or blocked, this value is ignored.

ciiCircSmallHellos.name: ciiCircSmallHellos
ciiCircSmallHellos.description: Can we send unpadded hellos on LAN circuits? 'false' means LAN Hellos must be padded. Implementations should allow the administrator to read this value. An implementation need not be able to support unpadded hellos to be conformant.

ciiCircLastUpTime.name: ciiCircLastUpTime
ciiCircLastUpTime.description: If the circuit is enabled, the value of sysUpTime when ciiCircAdminState most recently entered the state 'on'. If the circuit is not 'on', the value of sysUpTime when the circuit last entered state 'on', 0 if the circuit has never been 'on'.

ciiCirc3WayEnabled.name: ciiCirc3WayEnabled
ciiCirc3WayEnabled.description: Is this circuit enabled to run 3Way handshake?

ciiCircExtendedCircID.name: ciiCircExtendedCircID
ciiCircExtendedCircID.description: The value to be used as the extended circuit ID in 3Way handshake. This value is only used if ciiCirc3WayEnabled is true, and must be unique across all circuits on this IS.

ciiCircLevelTable.name: ciiCircLevelTable
ciiCircLevelTable.description: Level specific information about circuits used by IS-IS

ciiCircLevelEntry.name: ciiCircLevelEntry
ciiCircLevelEntry.description: An ciiCircLevelEntry exists for each level on each circuit used by Integrated IS-IS on this system.

ciiCircLevelIndex.name: ciiCircLevelIndex
ciiCircLevelIndex.description: The level that this entry describes.

ciiCircLevelMetric.name: ciiCircLevelMetric
ciiCircLevelMetric.description: The metric value of this circuit for this level.

ciiCircLevelWideMetric.name: ciiCircLevelWideMetric
ciiCircLevelWideMetric.description: The wide metric value of this circuit for this level.

ciiCircLevelISPriority.name: ciiCircLevelISPriority
ciiCircLevelISPriority.description: The priority for becoming LAN Designated Intermediate System at this level.

ciiCircLevelIDOctet.name: ciiCircLevelIDOctet
ciiCircLevelIDOctet.description: A one byte identifier that can be used in protocol packets to identify a circuit. Values of ciiCircLevelIDOctet do not need to be unique. They are only required to differ on LANs where the Intermediate System is the Designated Intermediate System.

ciiCircLevelID.name: ciiCircLevelID
ciiCircLevelID.description: On a point to point circuit with a fully initialized adjacency to a peer IS, the value of this object is the circuit ID negotiated during adjacency initialization. On a point to point circuit without such an adjacency, the value is the concatenation of the local system ID and the one byte ciiCircLevelIDOctet for this circuit i.e. the value that would be proposed for the circuit ID. On other circuit types, the value returned is the zero length OCTET STRING.

ciiCircLevelDesIS.name: ciiCircLevelDesIS
ciiCircLevelDesIS.description: The ID of the LAN Designated Intermediate System on this circuit at this level. If, for any reason, this system is not partaking in the relevant Designated Intermediate System election process, then the value returned is the zero length OCTET STRING.

ciiCircLevelHelloMultiplier.name: ciiCircLevelHelloMultiplier
ciiCircLevelHelloMultiplier.description: This value is multiplied by the corresponding HelloTimer and the result in seconds (rounded up) is used as the holding time in transmitted hellos, to be used by receivers of hello packets from this IS

ciiCircLevelHelloTimer.name: ciiCircLevelHelloTimer
ciiCircLevelHelloTimer.description: Maximum period, in milliseconds, between IIH PDUs on multiaccess networks at this level for LANs. The value at L1 is used as the period between Hellos on L1L2 point to point circuits. Setting this value at level 2 on an L1L2 point to point circuit will result in an error of InconsistentValue. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior.

ciiCircLevelDRHelloTimer.name: ciiCircLevelDRHelloTimer
ciiCircLevelDRHelloTimer.description: Period, in milliseconds, between Hello PDUs on multiaccess networks when this IS is the Designated Intermediate System. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior.

ciiCircLevelLSPThrottle.name: ciiCircLevelLSPThrottle
ciiCircLevelLSPThrottle.description: Minimal interval of time, in milliseconds, between transmissions of LSPs on an interface at this level.

ciiCircLevelMinLSPRetransInt.name: ciiCircLevelMinLSPRetransInt
ciiCircLevelMinLSPRetransInt.description: Minimum interval, in seconds, between re-transmission of an LSP at this level. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior. Note that ciiCircLevelLSPThrottle controls how fast we send back to back LSPs. This variable controls how fast we re-send the same LSP.

ciiCircLevelCSNPInterval.name: ciiCircLevelCSNPInterval
ciiCircLevelCSNPInterval.description: Interval of time, in seconds, between periodic transmission of a complete set of CSNPs on multiaccess networks if this router is the designated router at this level. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior.

ciiCircLevelPartSNPInterval.name: ciiCircLevelPartSNPInterval
ciiCircLevelPartSNPInterval.description: Minimum interval in seconds between sending Partial Sequence Number PDUs at this level. This object follows the resettingTimer behavior.

ciiSystemCounterTable.name: ciiSystemCounterTable
ciiSystemCounterTable.description: System wide counters for this Intermediate System.

ciiSysStatLevel.name: ciiSysStatLevel
ciiSysStatLevel.description: The level that this entry describes.

ciiSysStatCorrLSPs.name: ciiSysStatCorrLSPs
ciiSysStatCorrLSPs.description: Number of corrupted in-memory LSP frames detected. LSPs received from the wire with a bad checksum are silently dropped and not counted. LSPs received from the wire with parse errors are counted by ciiSysStatLSPErrors.

ciiSysStatAuthTypeFails.name: ciiSysStatAuthTypeFails
ciiSysStatAuthTypeFails.description: The number of frames with authentication type mismatches recognized by this Intermediate System.

ciiSysStatAuthFails.name: ciiSysStatAuthFails
ciiSysStatAuthFails.description: The number of frames with authentication failures recognized by this Intermediate System.

ciiSysStatLSPDbaseOloads.name: ciiSysStatLSPDbaseOloads
ciiSysStatLSPDbaseOloads.description: Number of times the LSP database has become overloaded.

ciiSysStatManAddrDropFromAreas.name: ciiSysStatManAddrDropFromAreas
ciiSysStatManAddrDropFromAreas.description: Number of times a manual address has been dropped from the area.

ciiSysStatAttmptToExMaxSeqNums.name: ciiSysStatAttmptToExMaxSeqNums
ciiSysStatAttmptToExMaxSeqNums.description: Number of times the IS has attempted to exceed the maximum sequence number.

ciiSysStatSeqNumSkips.name: ciiSysStatSeqNumSkips
ciiSysStatSeqNumSkips.description: Number of times a sequence number skip has occurred.

ciiSysStatOwnLSPPurges.name: ciiSysStatOwnLSPPurges
ciiSysStatOwnLSPPurges.description: Number of times a zero-aged copy of the system's own LSP is received from some other node.

ciiSysStatIDFieldLenMismatches.name: ciiSysStatIDFieldLenMismatches
ciiSysStatIDFieldLenMismatches.description: Number of times a PDU is received with a different value for ID field length to that of the receiving system.

ciiSysStatSPFRuns.name: ciiSysStatSPFRuns
ciiSysStatSPFRuns.description: Number of times we ran SPF at this level.

ciiSysStatLSPErrors.name: ciiSysStatLSPErrors
ciiSysStatLSPErrors.description: Number of LSP frames with errors we have received.

ciiCircuitCounterTable.name: ciiCircuitCounterTable
ciiCircuitCounterTable.description: Circuit specific counters for this Intermediate System.

ciiCircuitCounterEntry.name: ciiCircuitCounterEntry
ciiCircuitCounterEntry.description: An ciiCircuitCounterEntry exists for each circuit used by Integrated IS-IS on this system.

ciiCircuitType.name: ciiCircuitType
ciiCircuitType.description: What type of circuit saw these counts? The point to point Hello PDU includes both L1 and L2, and ISs form a single adjacency on point to point links. Thus we combine counts on point to point links into one group.

ciiCircAdjChanges.name: ciiCircAdjChanges
ciiCircAdjChanges.description: The number of times an adjacency state change has occurred on this circuit.

ciiCircNumAdj.name: ciiCircNumAdj
ciiCircNumAdj.description: The number of adjacencies on this circuit.

ciiCircInitFails.name: ciiCircInitFails
ciiCircInitFails.description: The number of times initialization of this circuit has failed. This counts events such as PPP NCP failures. Failures to form an adjacency are counted by ciiCircRejAdjs.

ciiCircRejAdjs.name: ciiCircRejAdjs
ciiCircRejAdjs.description: The number of times an adjacency has been rejected on this circuit.

ciiCircIDFieldLenMismatches.name: ciiCircIDFieldLenMismatches
ciiCircIDFieldLenMismatches.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with an ID field length different to that for this system has been received.

ciiCircMaxAreaAddrMismatches.name: ciiCircMaxAreaAddrMismatches
ciiCircMaxAreaAddrMismatches.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with a max area address field different to that for this system has been received.

ciiCircAuthTypeFails.name: ciiCircAuthTypeFails
ciiCircAuthTypeFails.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with an auth type field different to that for this system has been received.

ciiCircAuthFails.name: ciiCircAuthFails
ciiCircAuthFails.description: The number of times an IS-IS control PDU with the correct auth type has failed to pass authentication validation.

ciiCircLANDesISChanges.name: ciiCircLANDesISChanges
ciiCircLANDesISChanges.description: The number of times the Designated IS has changed on this circuit at this level. If the circuit is point to point, this count is zero.

ciiPacketCounterTable.name: ciiPacketCounterTable
ciiPacketCounterTable.description: Information about IS-IS protocol traffic at one level on one circuit in one direction

ciiPacketCounterEntry.name: ciiPacketCounterEntry
ciiPacketCounterEntry.description: Information about IS-IS protocol traffic at one level on one circuit in one direction

ciiPacketCountLevel.name: ciiPacketCountLevel
ciiPacketCountLevel.description: The level at which these PDU counts have been collected.

ciiPacketCountDirection.name: ciiPacketCountDirection
ciiPacketCountDirection.description: Were we sending or receiving these PDUs?

ciiPacketCountIIHellos.name: ciiPacketCountIIHellos
ciiPacketCountIIHellos.description: The number of IS-IS Hello PDU frames seen in this direction at this level. Point-to-Point IIH PDUs are counted at the lowest enabled level: at L1 on L1 or L1L2 circuits, and at L2 otherwise.

ciiPacketCountISHellos.name: ciiPacketCountISHellos
ciiPacketCountISHellos.description: The number of ES-IS Hello PDU frames seen in this direction. ISH PDUs are counted at the lowest enabled level: at L1 on L1 or L1L2 circuits, and at L2 otherwise.

ciiPacketCountESHellos.name: ciiPacketCountESHellos
ciiPacketCountESHellos.description: The number of ES Hello PDU frames seen in this direction. ESH PDUs are counted at the lowest enabled level: at L1 on L1 or L1L2 circuits, and at L2 otherwise.

ciiPacketCountLSPs.name: ciiPacketCountLSPs
ciiPacketCountLSPs.description: The number of IS-IS LSP frames seen in this direction at this level.

ciiPacketCountCSNPs.name: ciiPacketCountCSNPs
ciiPacketCountCSNPs.description: The number of IS-IS CSNP frames seen in this direction at this level.

ciiPacketCountPSNPs.name: ciiPacketCountPSNPs
ciiPacketCountPSNPs.description: The number of IS-IS PSNP frames seen in this direction at this level.

ciiPacketCountUnknowns.name: ciiPacketCountUnknowns
ciiPacketCountUnknowns.description: The number of unknown IS-IS PDU frames seen at this level.

ciiISAdjTable.name: ciiISAdjTable
ciiISAdjTable.description: The table of adjacencies to Intermediate Systems.

ciiISAdjEntry.name: ciiISAdjEntry
ciiISAdjEntry.description: Each entry corresponds to one adjacency to an Intermediate System on this system.

ciiISAdjIndex.name: ciiISAdjIndex
ciiISAdjIndex.description: A unique value identifying the IS adjacency from all other such adjacencies on this circuit. This value is automatically assigned by the system when the adjacency is created.

ciiISAdj3WayState.name: ciiISAdj3WayState
ciiISAdj3WayState.description: The 3Way state of the adjacency. These are picked to match the historical on-the-wire representation of the 3Way state, and are not intended to match ciiISAdjState.

ciiISAdjNeighSNPAAddress.name: ciiISAdjNeighSNPAAddress
ciiISAdjNeighSNPAAddress.description: The SNPA address of the neighboring system.

ciiISAdjNeighSysType.name: ciiISAdjNeighSysType
ciiISAdjNeighSysType.description: The type of the neighboring system.

ciiISAdjNeighSysID.name: ciiISAdjNeighSysID
ciiISAdjNeighSysID.description: The system ID of the neighboring Intermediate System.

ciiISAdjNbrExtendedCircID.name: ciiISAdjNbrExtendedCircID
ciiISAdjNbrExtendedCircID.description: The 4 byte Extended Circuit ID learned from the Neighbor during 3-way handshake, or 0.

ciiISAdjUsage.name: ciiISAdjUsage
ciiISAdjUsage.description: How is the adjacency used? On a point-to-point link, this might be level1and2, but on a LAN, the usage will be level1 on the adjacency between peers at L1, and level2 for the adjacency between peers at L2.

ciiISAdjHoldTimer.name: ciiISAdjHoldTimer
ciiISAdjHoldTimer.description: The holding time in seconds for this adjacency. This value is based on received IIH PDUs and the elapsed time since receipt.

ciiISAdjNeighPriority.name: ciiISAdjNeighPriority
ciiISAdjNeighPriority.description: Priority of the neighboring Intermediate System for becoming the Designated Intermediate System.

ciiISAdjLastUpTime.name: ciiISAdjLastUpTime
ciiISAdjLastUpTime.description: If the ciiISAdjState is in state 'up', the value of sysUpTime when the adjacency most recently entered the state 'up', or 0 if it has never been in state 'up'.

ciiISAdjAreaAddrTable.name: ciiISAdjAreaAddrTable
ciiISAdjAreaAddrTable.description: This table contains the set of Area Addresses of neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

ciiISAdjAreaAddrEntry.name: ciiISAdjAreaAddrEntry
ciiISAdjAreaAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one Area Address reported by a neighboring Intermediate System in its IIH PDUs.

ciiISAdjAreaAddrIndex.name: ciiISAdjAreaAddrIndex
ciiISAdjAreaAddrIndex.description: An index for the areas associated with one neighbor. This provides a simple way to walk the table.

ciiISAdjAreaAddress.name: ciiISAdjAreaAddress
ciiISAdjAreaAddress.description: One Area Address as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

ciiISAdjIPAddrTable.name: ciiISAdjIPAddrTable
ciiISAdjIPAddrTable.description: This table contains the set of IP Addresses of neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

ciiISAdjIPAddrEntry.name: ciiISAdjIPAddrEntry
ciiISAdjIPAddrEntry.description: Each entry contains one IP Address reported by a neighboring Intermediate System in its IIH PDUs.

ciiISAdjIPAddrIndex.name: ciiISAdjIPAddrIndex
ciiISAdjIPAddrIndex.description: An index to this table which identifies the IP addresses to which this entry belongs.

ciiISAdjIPAddrType.name: ciiISAdjIPAddrType
ciiISAdjIPAddrType.description: The type of one IP Address as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

ciiISAdjIPAddrAddress.name: ciiISAdjIPAddrAddress
ciiISAdjIPAddrAddress.description: One IP Address as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

ciiISAdjProtSuppTable.name: ciiISAdjProtSuppTable
ciiISAdjProtSuppTable.description: This table contains the set of protocols supported by neighboring Intermediate Systems as reported in received IIH PDUs.

ciiISAdjProtSuppEntry.name: ciiISAdjProtSuppEntry
ciiISAdjProtSuppEntry.description: Each entry contains one protocol supported by a neighboring Intermediate System as reported in its IIH PDUs.

ciiISAdjProtSuppProtocol.name: ciiISAdjProtSuppProtocol
ciiISAdjProtSuppProtocol.description: One supported protocol as reported in IIH PDUs received from the neighbor.

ciiRATable.name: ciiRATable
ciiRATable.description: The table of Reachable Addresses to NSAPs or Address Prefixes.

ciiRAEntry.name: ciiRAEntry
ciiRAEntry.description: Each entry defines a Reachable Address to a NSAP or Address Prefix.

ciiRAIndex.name: ciiRAIndex
ciiRAIndex.description: The identifier for this ciiRAEntry. This value must be unique amongst all Reachable Addresses on the same parent Circuit. This object follows the index and ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

ciiRAExistState.name: ciiRAExistState
ciiRAExistState.description: The existence state of this Reachable Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

ciiRAAdminState.name: ciiRAAdminState
ciiRAAdminState.description: The administrative state of the Reachable Address. This object follows the CiiAdminState and ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

ciiRAAddrPrefix.name: ciiRAAddrPrefix
ciiRAAddrPrefix.description: The destination of this Reachable Address. This is an Address Prefix. This object follows the replaceOnlyWhileDisabled and ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

ciiRAMapType.name: ciiRAMapType
ciiRAMapType.description: The type of mapping to be employed to ascertain the SNPA Address which should be used in forwarding PDUs for this Reachable Address prefix. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior. The following values of mapping type are defined: none: The mapping is null because the neighbor SNPA is implicit by nature of the subnetwork (e.g. a point-to-point linkage). explicit: The subnetwork addresses in the object ciiRASNPAAddress is to be used. extractIDI: The SNPA is embedded in the IDI of the destination NSAP Address. The mapping algorithm extracts the SNPA to be used according to the format and encoding rules of ISO8473/Add2. This SNPA extraction algorithm can be used in conjunction with Reachable Address prefixes from the X.121, F.69, E.163 and E.164 addressing subdomains. extractDSP: All, or a suffix, of the SNPA is embedded in the DSP of the destination address. This SNPA extraction algorithm extracts the embedded subnetwork addressing information by performing a logical AND of the ciiRASNPAMask object value with the destination address. The part of the SNPA extracted from the destination NSAP is appended to the ciiRASNPAPrefix object value to form the next hop subnetwork addressing information.

ciiRAMetric.name: ciiRAMetric
ciiRAMetric.description: The metric value for reaching the specified prefix over this circuit. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

ciiRAMetricType.name: ciiRAMetricType
ciiRAMetricType.description: Indicates whether the metric is internal or external. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

ciiRASNPAAddress.name: ciiRASNPAAddress
ciiRASNPAAddress.description: The SNPA Address to which a PDU may be forwarded in order to reach a destination which matches the address prefix of the Reachable Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

ciiRASNPAMask.name: ciiRASNPAMask
ciiRASNPAMask.description: A bit mask with 1 bits indicating the positions in the effective destination address from which embedded SNPA information is to be extracted. For the extraction the first octet of the ciiRASNPAMask object value is aligned with the first octet (AFI) of the NSAP Address. If the ciiRASNPAMask object value and NSAP Address are of different lengths, the shorter of the two is logically padded with zeros before performing the extraction. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

ciiRASNPAPrefix.name: ciiRASNPAPrefix
ciiRASNPAPrefix.description: A fixed SNPA prefix for use when the ciiRAMapType is extractDSP. The SNPA Address to use is formed by concatenating the fixed SNPA prefix with a variable SNPA part that is extracted from the effective destination address. For Reachable Address prefixes in which the entire SNPA is embedded in the DSP the SNPA Prefix shall be null. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

ciiRAType.name: ciiRAType
ciiRAType.description: The type of Reachable address. Those of type manual are created by the network manager. Those of type automatic are created through propagation of routing information from another routing protocol (eg. IDRP).

ciiIPRATable.name: ciiIPRATable
ciiIPRATable.description: The table of IP Reachable Addresses to networks, subnetworks or hosts either manually configured or learned from another protocol.

ciiIPRAEntry.name: ciiIPRAEntry
ciiIPRAEntry.description: Each entry defines an IP Reachable Address to a network, subnetwork or host. Each IP Reachable Address may have multiple entries in the table, one for each equal cost path to the reachable address.

ciiIPRADestType.name: ciiIPRADestType
ciiIPRADestType.description: The type of this IP Reachable Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

ciiIPRADest.name: ciiIPRADest
ciiIPRADest.description: The destination of this IP Reachable Address. This is either a network address, subnetwork address or host address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

ciiIPRADestPrefixLen.name: ciiIPRADestPrefixLen
ciiIPRADestPrefixLen.description: The length of the IP Netmask for Reachability Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

ciiIPRANextHopIndex.name: ciiIPRANextHopIndex
ciiIPRANextHopIndex.description: Index of next hop. Used when there are multiple Equal Cost Multipath alternatives for the same destination.

ciiIPRANextHopType.name: ciiIPRANextHopType
ciiIPRANextHopType.description: The type of the IP next hop address.

ciiIPRANextHop.name: ciiIPRANextHop
ciiIPRANextHop.description: The IP next hop to this destination.

ciiIPRAType.name: ciiIPRAType
ciiIPRAType.description: The type of this IP Reachable Address. Those of type manual are created by the network manager. Those of type automatic are created through propagation of routing information from another routing protocol. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

ciiIPRAExistState.name: ciiIPRAExistState
ciiIPRAExistState.description: The state of this IP Reachable Address. This object follows the ExistenceState and ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

ciiIPRAAdminState.name: ciiIPRAAdminState
ciiIPRAAdminState.description: The administrative state of the IP Reachable Address. This object follows the CiiAdminState and ManualOrAutomatic behaviors.

ciiIPRAMetric.name: ciiIPRAMetric
ciiIPRAMetric.description: The metric value for reaching the specified destination over this circuit. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

ciiIPRAMetricType.name: ciiIPRAMetricType
ciiIPRAMetricType.description: Indicates whether the metric is internal or external. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

ciiIPRAFullMetric.name: ciiIPRAFullMetric
ciiIPRAFullMetric.description: The wide metric value for reaching the specified destination over this circuit. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

ciiIPRASNPAAddress.name: ciiIPRASNPAAddress
ciiIPRASNPAAddress.description: The SNPA Address to which a PDU may be forwarded in order to reach a destination which matches this IP Reachable Address. This object follows the ManualOrAutomatic behavior.

ciiLSPSummaryEntry.name: ciiLSPSummaryEntry
ciiLSPSummaryEntry.description: Each entry provides a summary describing an LSP currently stored in the system.

ciiLSPLevel.name: ciiLSPLevel
ciiLSPLevel.description: At which level does this LSP appear?

ciiLSPID.name: ciiLSPID
ciiLSPID.description: The 8 byte LSP ID, consisting of the SystemID, Circuit ID, and Fragment Number.

ciiLSPSeq.name: ciiLSPSeq
ciiLSPSeq.description: The sequence number for this LSP.

ciiLSPZeroLife.name: ciiLSPZeroLife
ciiLSPZeroLife.description: Is this LSP being purged by this System?

ciiLSPLifetimeRemain.name: ciiLSPLifetimeRemain
ciiLSPLifetimeRemain.description: The remaining lifetime in seconds for this LSP.

ciiLSPTLVEntry.name: ciiLSPTLVEntry
ciiLSPTLVEntry.description: Each entry describes an LSP current stored in the system.

ciiLSPTLVIndex.name: ciiLSPTLVIndex
ciiLSPTLVIndex.description: The index of this TLV in the LSP. The first TLV has index 1 and the Nth TLV has an index of N.

ciiLSPTLVSeq.name: ciiLSPTLVSeq
ciiLSPTLVSeq.description: The sequence number for this LSP.

ciiPduLspId.name: ciiPduLspId
ciiPduLspId.description: An Octet String that uniquely identifies a Link State PDU.

ciiPduFragment.name: ciiPduFragment
ciiPduFragment.description: Holds up to 64 initial bytes of a PDU that triggered the notification.

ciiPduFieldLen.name: ciiPduFieldLen
ciiPduFieldLen.description: Holds the System ID length reported in PDU we received.

ciiPduMaxAreaAddress.name: ciiPduMaxAreaAddress
ciiPduMaxAreaAddress.description: Holds the Max Area Addresses reported in a PDU we received.

ciiPduProtocolVersion.name: ciiPduProtocolVersion
ciiPduProtocolVersion.description: Holds the Protocol version reported in PDU we received.

ciiPduLspSize.name: ciiPduLspSize
ciiPduLspSize.description: Holds the size of LSP we received that is too big to forward.

ciiPduOriginatingBufferSize.name: ciiPduOriginatingBufferSize
ciiPduOriginatingBufferSize.description: Holds the size of ciiSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize advertised by the peer in the originatingLSPBufferSize TLV.

ciiPduProtocolsSupported.name: ciiPduProtocolsSupported
ciiPduProtocolsSupported.description: The list of protocols supported by an adjacent system. This may be empty.

ciiAdjState.name: ciiAdjState
ciiAdjState.description: The current state of an adjacency.

ciiErrorOffset.name: ciiErrorOffset
ciiErrorOffset.description: An offset to a problem in a PDU. If the problem is a malformed TLV, this points to the beginning of the TLV. If the problem is in the header, this points to the byte that is suspicious.

ciiErrorTLVType.name: ciiErrorTLVType
ciiErrorTLVType.description: The type for a malformed TLV.

ciiNotifManualAddress.name: ciiNotifManualAddress
ciiNotifManualAddress.description: Manually configured area address used in this notification.

ciiNotifIsLevelIndex.name: ciiNotifIsLevelIndex
ciiNotifIsLevelIndex.description: The index value used in this notification to indicate the system level.

ciiDatabaseOverload.name: ciiDatabaseOverload
ciiDatabaseOverload.description: This notification is generated when the system enters or leaves the Overload state. The number of times this has be generated and cleared is kept track of by ciiSysStatLSPDbaseOloads.

ciiManualAddressDrops.name: ciiManualAddressDrops
ciiManualAddressDrops.description: This notification is generated when one of the manual areaAddresses assigned to this system is ignored when computing routes. The object ciiNotifManualAddress describes the area that has been dropped. The number of times this event has been generated is counted by ciiSysStatManAddrDropFromAreas. This notification is edge triggered, and should not be regenerated until an address that was used in the previous computation has been dropped.

ciiCorruptedLSPDetected.name: ciiCorruptedLSPDetected
ciiCorruptedLSPDetected.description: This notification is generated when we find that an LSP that was stored in memory has become corrupted. The number of times this has been generated is counted by ciiSysStatCorrLSPs. We forward an LSP ID. We may have independent knowledge of the ID, but in some implementations there is a chance that the ID itself will be corrupted.

ciiAttemptToExceedMaxSequence.name: ciiAttemptToExceedMaxSequence
ciiAttemptToExceedMaxSequence.description: When the sequence number on an LSP we generate wraps the 32 bit sequence counter, we purge and wait to re-announce this information. This notification describes that event. Since these should not be generated rapidly, we generate an event each time this happens. While the first 6 bytes of the LSPID are ours, the other two contain useful information.

ciiIDLenMismatch.name: ciiIDLenMismatch
ciiIDLenMismatch.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with a different value of the System ID Length. This notification includes an index to identify the circuit where we saw the PDU and the header of the PDU which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received on the same circuit.

ciiMaxAreaAddressesMismatch.name: ciiMaxAreaAddressesMismatch
ciiMaxAreaAddressesMismatch.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with a different value of the Maximum Area Addresses. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from the same circuit.

ciiOwnLSPPurge.name: ciiOwnLSPPurge
ciiOwnLSPPurge.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with our systemID and zero age. This notification includes the circuit Index and router ID from the LSP, if available, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion.

ciiSequenceNumberSkip.name: ciiSequenceNumberSkip
ciiSequenceNumberSkip.description: When we receive an LSP with our System ID and different contents, we may need to reissue the LSP with a higher sequence number. We send this notification if we need to increase the sequence number by more than one. If two Intermediate Systems are configured with the same System ID, this notification will fire.

ciiAuthenticationTypeFailure.name: ciiAuthenticationTypeFailure
ciiAuthenticationTypeFailure.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with the wrong authentication type field. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from the same circuit.

ciiAuthenticationFailure.name: ciiAuthenticationFailure
ciiAuthenticationFailure.description: A notification sent when we receive a PDU with incorrect authentication information field. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from the same circuit.

ciiVersionSkew.name: ciiVersionSkew
ciiVersionSkew.description: A notification sent when we receive a Hello PDU from an IS running a different version of the protocol. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from the same circuit.

ciiAreaMismatch.name: ciiAreaMismatch
ciiAreaMismatch.description: A notification sent when we receive a Hello PDU from an IS which does not share any area address. This notification includes the header of the packet, which may help a network manager identify the source of the confusion. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from the same circuit.

ciiRejectedAdjacency.name: ciiRejectedAdjacency
ciiRejectedAdjacency.description: A notification sent when we receive a Hello PDU from an IS, but do not establish an adjacency for some reason. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from the circuit.

ciiLSPTooLargeToPropagate.name: ciiLSPTooLargeToPropagate
ciiLSPTooLargeToPropagate.description: A notification sent when we attempt to propagate an LSP which is larger than the dataLinkBlockSize for the circuit. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from the same circuit.

ciiOrigLSPBuffSizeMismatch.name: ciiOrigLSPBuffSizeMismatch
ciiOrigLSPBuffSizeMismatch.description: A notification sent when a Level 1 LSP or Level 2 LSP is received which is larger than the local value for ciiSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize, or when an LSP is received containing the originatingLSPBufferSize option and the value in the PDU option field does not match the local value for ciiSysLevelOrigLSPBuffSize. We pass up the size from the option field or the size of the LSP that exceeds our configuration. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from the same circuit.

ciiProtocolsSupportedMismatch.name: ciiProtocolsSupportedMismatch
ciiProtocolsSupportedMismatch.description: A notification sent when a non-pseudonode segment 0 LSP is received that has no matching protocols supported. This may be because the system does not generate the field, or because there are no common elements. The list of protocols supported should be included in the notification: it may be empty if the TLV is not supported, or if the TLV is empty. This should be an edge-triggered notification. We should not send a second notification about PDUs received from the same circuit.

ciiAdjacencyChange.name: ciiAdjacencyChange
ciiAdjacencyChange.description: A notification sent when an adjacency changes state, entering or leaving state up. The first 6 bytes of the ciiPduLspId are the SystemID of the adjacent IS. The ciiAdjState is the new state of the adjacency.

ciiLSPErrorDetected.name: ciiLSPErrorDetected
ciiLSPErrorDetected.description: This notification is generated when we receive an LSP with a parse error. The ciiCircIfIndex holds in index of the circuit on which the PDU arrived. The ciiPduFragment holds start of the LSP, and the ciiErrorOffset points to the problem. If the problem is a mal-formed TLV, ciiErrorOffset points to start of the TLV and ciiErrorTLVType holds the value of the type. If the problem is with the LSP header, ciiErrorOffset points to the suspicious byte. The number of such LSPs is accumulated in ciiSysStatLSPErrors.

ciscoIetfIsisMIBCompliance.name: ciscoIetfIsisMIBCompliance
ciscoIetfIsisMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for agents that support the IS-IS MIB

ciscoIetfIsisMIBAdvCompliance.name: ciscoIetfIsisMIBAdvCompliance
ciscoIetfIsisMIBAdvCompliance.description: The compliance statement for agents that support the IS-IS MIB

ciscoIetfIsisSystemGroup.name: ciscoIetfIsisSystemGroup
ciscoIetfIsisSystemGroup.description: The collections of objects used to manage an IS-IS router.

ciscoIetfIsisCircuitGroup.name: ciscoIetfIsisCircuitGroup
ciscoIetfIsisCircuitGroup.description: The collection of objects used to describe in IS-IS Circuit.

ciscoIetfIsisISAdjGroup.name: ciscoIetfIsisISAdjGroup
ciscoIetfIsisISAdjGroup.description: The collections of objects used to manage an IS-IS Adjacency.

ciscoIetfIsisNotifObjectGroup.name: ciscoIetfIsisNotifObjectGroup
ciscoIetfIsisNotifObjectGroup.description: The objects used to record notification parameters.

ciscoIetfIsisNotificationGroup.name: ciscoIetfIsisNotificationGroup
ciscoIetfIsisNotificationGroup.description: The collections of notifications sent by an IS.

ciscoIetfIsisISPDUCounterGroup.name: ciscoIetfIsisISPDUCounterGroup
ciscoIetfIsisISPDUCounterGroup.description: The collections of objects used to count protocol PDUs.

ciscoIetfIsisRATableGroup.name: ciscoIetfIsisRATableGroup
ciscoIetfIsisRATableGroup.description: The collections of objects used to manage the reachable NSAP prefixes.

ciscoIetfIsisISIPRADestGroup.name: ciscoIetfIsisISIPRADestGroup
ciscoIetfIsisISIPRADestGroup.description: The collections of objects used to manage configured IP addresses.

ciscoIetfIsisLSPGroup.name: ciscoIetfIsisLSPGroup
ciscoIetfIsisLSPGroup.description: The collections of objects used to observe the LSP Data Base.
